<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="78" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="78">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="78">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Z. W. Wang &amp; H. C. Xi" authorityYear="2019" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Dysosma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dysosma villosa" order="Ranunculales" pageId="1" pageNumber="78" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="78">Dysosma villosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Berberidaceae" genus="D." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="D. difformis" order="Ranunculales" pageId="1" pageNumber="78" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="difformis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="78">D. difformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Hemsl. &amp; E.H.Wilson) T.H.Wang 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="78">ex</emphasis>
T.S.Ying, but differs from the latter by its inflorescences generally with more flowers (5-13 vs. 2-5), white-villous petioles, stems and abaxial leaf blade and dark purple-red stigma.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
